                  'Harden calculator.py. Wrap the number inputs in a helper read_number(prompt: str) -> float that loops until the user types a valid float, catching ValueError and printing "Please enter a valid number." Also reject menu choices that are not 1–7 with "Invalid choice, try again." and continue the loop without crashing. In the divide and modulo branches, catch ZeroDivisionError and print "Cannot divide by zero." then continue.',
