            overview: 'A capstone that turns raw machine sensor streams into a failure-prediction classifier. Engineer rolling-window statistics over time, label each window with whether failure occurred in the next N hours, train RF + XGBoost, and ship the model with proper time-aware validation (no leakage from the future).',
            functionalRequirements: [
              'Ingest a sensor CSV (NASA C-MAPSS or AI4I 2020 Predictive Maintenance) per-machine, per-cycle.',
              'Engineer rolling features: mean, std, min, max over windows of 5/10/30 cycles for each sensor.',
              'Define the binary target as **failure within next H cycles** (configurable, default H=15).',
              'Use **TimeSeriesSplit** (or per-machine GroupKFold) for cross-validation — never random shuffle.',
              'Train and compare **RandomForestClassifier** and **XGBClassifier**; tune the better one.',
              'Output a maintenance-priority table: top 10 machines by predicted failure probability.',
            ],
            technicalImplementation: [
              '**Stack:** Python 3.10+, Pandas, scikit-learn, xgboost, joblib.',
              '**File layout:** `src/load.py`, `src/features.py`, `src/labels.py`, `src/train.py`, `src/predict.py`, `main.py`.',
              '**Feature engineering:** vectorized rolling via `groupby("machine_id").rolling(w)` for each window size.',
              '**Splits:** TimeSeriesSplit with 5 folds — past predicts future only.',
              '**Metric:** F2 (recall-weighted) since false negatives are very expensive in maintenance.',
              '**Outputs:** `models/pdm.joblib`, `out/feature_importance.png`, `out/priority_list.csv`.',
            ],
            prompts: [
              { step: 1, label: 'Load and explore', outcome: 'Per-machine sensor frame, label-leakage understanding.', prompt: 'Create src/load.py with load_cmapss(train_path, test_path, rul_path) returning train/test DataFrames with columns machine_id, cycle, op_setting_1..3, sensor_1..21. Add a quick EDA cell in notebooks/eda.ipynb: row counts, machines per file, distribution of last-cycle counts (= time-to-failure proxy). Note explicitly that NASA C-MAPSS has different test labelling — RUL is given separately.' },
              { step: 2, label: 'Rolling-window features', outcome: 'Engineered training matrix.', prompt: 'Create src/features.py with build_features(df, sensor_cols, windows=(5,10,30)) -> pd.DataFrame. For each (sensor, window, stat in [mean, std, min, max]) add a column f"{sensor}_w{window}_{stat}". Use df.groupby("machine_id")[sensor_cols].rolling(window).agg(stat) and align the index back. Drop the first max(windows)-1 cycles per machine to avoid NaN rows.' },
              { step: 3, label: 'Failure labels', outcome: 'Target column without leakage.', prompt: 'Create src/labels.py with add_labels(df, horizon=15). For each machine, compute remaining_cycles = max(cycle) - cycle within that machine. Set y = (remaining_cycles <= horizon).astype(int). For C-MAPSS test data, use the provided RUL file: y = (RUL_at_that_cycle <= horizon). Return df with a y column.' },
              { step: 4, label: 'Time-aware CV training', outcome: 'No-leakage performance estimates.', prompt: 'Create src/train.py with cross_validate_model(model, X, y, groups, n_splits=5) using sklearn.model_selection.TimeSeriesSplit. Score with f2 (use sklearn.metrics.fbeta_score, beta=2) and recall. Train RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=400, class_weight="balanced", random_state=42) and XGBClassifier(scale_pos_weight=ratio). Pick the better one by mean F2.' },
              { step: 5, label: 'Tune and explain', outcome: 'Tuned XGB + feature importance plot.', prompt: 'In src/train.py add tune_xgb(X, y) using GridSearchCV(TimeSeriesSplit(5)) over n_estimators [200,400,800], max_depth [4,6,8], learning_rate [0.05,0.1], scale_pos_weight [neg/pos ratio]. Then plot top 20 feature importances (use model.feature_importances_) to out/feature_importance.png. Save the fitted pipeline to models/pdm.joblib.' },
              { step: 6, label: 'Inference + priority list', outcome: 'A daily list of machines to inspect.', prompt: 'Create src/predict.py with predict_priority(model, latest_features_df) -> pd.DataFrame sorted by failure probability desc with columns machine_id, prob_fail_within_horizon, last_cycle, top_3_contributing_features (use SHAP if installed, else rank by sklearn permutation_importance once at fit time and cache top features per machine via top contributing sensor reading). Save top 10 to out/priority_list.csv. Wire main.py: load → features → labels → train → save model → produce priority list.' },
            ],
